cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on a novel secured outsourced content-based image retrieval solution that uses homomorphic encryption to protect the privacy of the images. This falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with image retrieval and signature extraction, which are core topics in computer vision and pattern recognition. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a solution for outsourced image retrieval, which involves distributed computing in the cloud. 
4. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper deals with the storage and retrieval of images from a cloud-based database, which falls under the domain of databases. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image retrieval, which is a core topic in multimedia.
